==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Testamur
<hw>Tes*ta"mur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., we
testify, fr. <ets>testari</ets> to testify.]</ety> <fld>(Eng.
Universities)</fld> <def>A certificate of merit or proficiency; -- so
called from the Latin words, <xex>Ita testamur</xex>, with which it
commences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Testate</ent>⟦br⟧
